{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DtVeRqqw5Sid5fV52riYaF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Constraint;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Payload;\n     5→import java.lang.annotation.*;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.validator.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator;\n     7→\n     8→@Target({ElementType.TYPE})\n     9→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    10→@Constraint(validatedBy = AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator.class)\n    11→@Documented\n    12→public @interface AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull {\n    13→\n    14→  String message() default \"At least one field must be not null\";\n    15→\n    16→  Class<?>[] groups() default {};\n    17→\n    18→  Class<? extends Payload>[] payload() default {};\n    19→\n    20→  String[] fieldNames() default {};\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"e34c9da5-b06f-4f6b-8eff-c01c6e2f077e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QAiMQLfm6rsp9YksFeAyny","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintValidator;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintValidatorContext;\n     5→import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n     7→\n     8→public class AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator\n     9→    implements ConstraintValidator<AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull, Object> {\n    10→\n    11→  private String[] fieldNames;\n    12→\n    13→  public void initialize(AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull constraintAnnotation) {\n    14→    fieldNames = constraintAnnotation.fieldNames();\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public boolean isValid(Object object, ConstraintValidatorContext constraintValidatorContext) {\n    18→\n    19→    Class<?> clazz = object.getClass();\n    20→\n    21→    configFieldNamesIfEmpty(clazz);\n    22→\n    23→    for (String propertyName : fieldNames) {\n    24→      Field field = getDeclaredField(clazz, propertyName);\n    25→      if (getValue(field, object) != null) {\n    26→        return true;\n    27→      }\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    return false;\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  private void configFieldNamesIfEmpty(Class<?> clazz) {\n    34→\n    35→    if (fieldNames.length == 0) {\n    36→      fieldNames = getInstanceDeclaredFieldNames(clazz);\n    37→    }\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  private String[] getInstanceDeclaredFieldNames(Class<?> clazz) {\n    41→\n    42→    Field[] fields = clazz.getDeclaredFields();\n    43→\n    44→    String[] resultNames = new String[fields.length];\n    45→\n    46→    for (int fieldIndex = 0; fieldIndex < fields.length; fieldIndex++) {\n    47→      resultNames[fieldIndex] = fields[fieldIndex].getName();\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    return resultNames;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  private Object getValue(Field field, Object instance) {\n    54→    Object value;\n    55→    try {\n    56→      value = field.get(instance);\n    57→    } catch (IllegalAccessException ex) {\n    58→      throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    59→    }\n    60→    return value;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  private Field getDeclaredField(Class<?> clazz, String name) {\n    64→    Field field;\n    65→    try {\n    66→      field = clazz.getDeclaredField(name);\n    67→      field.setAccessible(true);\n    68→    } catch (NoSuchFieldException ex) {\n    69→      throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    70→    }\n    71→    return field;\n    72→  }\n    73→}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"955f9ae6-baa1-47bd-87d4-1e1052026000"}
