{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012c1kPX2HB6Gx2NbRWFiPmn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've created a comprehensive Python smoke test script at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/smoke.py`.\n\n## Key Features:\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Accepts `BASE_URL` from environment variable or command line argument\n- Defaults to `http://localhost:8080`\n- Automatically appends `/api` prefix to all endpoints\n\n**Server Readiness:**\n- Waits up to 60 seconds for the server to be ready\n- Retries health check every 2 seconds\n- Tests the `/api/tags` endpoint as a health check\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n1. ✓ User registration with unique random credentials\n2. ✓ User login\n3. ✓ Get current user (authenticated)\n4. ✓ Create article (authenticated)\n5. ✓ Get articles list\n6. ✓ Get article by slug\n7. ✓ Create comment on article (authenticated)\n8. ✓ Get comments for article\n9. ✓ Get tags\n10. ✓ Get user profile\n11. ✓ Favorite article (authenticated)\n\n**Features:**\n- Uses `requests` library for HTTP calls\n- Generates unique random usernames/emails to avoid conflicts\n- Properly handles JWT token authentication with \"Token\" prefix\n- Prints clear PASS/FAIL status for each test\n- Returns exit code 0 if all tests pass, 1 if any fail\n- Comprehensive error handling with informative messages\n- Summary statistics at the end\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\n# Using environment variable\nBASE_URL=http://localhost:8080 python smoke.py\n\n# Using command line argument\npython smoke.py http://localhost:8080\n\n# Using default\npython smoke.py\n```\n\nThe script tests the complete user journey: registration, login, creating content (articles and comments), retrieving data, and social features (profiles and favorites)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"a9282798-2201-4d79-afaa-08a6af8273f1"}
