{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011MSFm5tAy7dYWiCRK6wNon","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully rewritten the application.properties file for Spring Boot. \n\n## Summary of Changes\n\nThe file at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/resources/application.properties` has been updated with Spring Boot equivalents:\n\n### Key Migrations:\n\n1. **REST API Path**: `quarkus.rest.path=/api` → `server.servlet.context-path=/api` (added port 8080)\n\n2. **Database Configuration**: Converted Quarkus datasource properties to Spring Boot format with explicit driver class\n\n3. **Hibernate/JPA**: `quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create` → `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop` with additional JPA properties\n\n4. **JWT Settings**: Converted MicroProfile JWT properties to custom JWT properties (these will need to be read by your custom JWT configuration in Spring Boot)\n\n5. **Additional Properties**: Added Spring Boot actuator configuration for health endpoints\n\nThe configuration maintains the same functional behavior while using Spring Boot's property conventions."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"494c4348-7bf9-427c-bb49-720e9e7b8d69"}
