{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018yq21h4GP9hFW1wviz52Ci","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All files have been successfully created. Let me provide a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nAll 8 files have been successfully created/updated for the Quarkus to Spring Boot migration:\n\n### 1. **JwtTokenProvider** \n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java`\n- **Changes**: Replaced SmallRye JWT (`io.smallrye.jwt`) with jjwt (`io.jsonwebtoken`)\n- Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`\n- Implemented JWT signing and validation with HMAC-SHA256\n- Added `validateTokenAndGetSubject()` method for token verification\n\n### 2. **BCryptHashProvider**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/BCryptHashProvider.java`\n- **Changes**: Replaced Quarkus Elytron `BcryptUtil` with Spring Security's `BCryptPasswordEncoder`\n- Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`\n\n### 3. **SlugifySlugProvider**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java`\n- **Changes**: Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`\n\n### 4. **SecurityConfig** (NEW)\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/SecurityConfig.java`\n- **Purpose**: Spring Security configuration with JWT authentication\n- Configures security filter chain with stateless session management\n- Defines public endpoints (user registration, login, article views)\n- Integrates JWT authentication filter\n\n### 5. **JwtAuthenticationFilter** (NEW)\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java`\n- **Purpose**: JWT authentication filter for Spring Security\n- Extracts JWT tokens from Authorization header (supports both \"Token\" and \"Bearer\" prefixes)\n- Validates tokens and sets Spring Security context\n\n### 6. **ExceptionMappers**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/ExceptionMappers.java`\n- **Changes**: Converted from Quarkus `@ServerExceptionMapper` to Spring `@RestControllerAdvice`\n- Replaced JAX-RS `Response` with Spring `ResponseEntity`\n- Replaced Quarkus exceptions with Spring Security's `BadCredentialsException`\n\n### 7. **BeanValidationExceptionMapper**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java`\n- **Changes**: Converted from JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper` to Spring `@RestControllerAdvice`\n- Replaced JAX-RS `Response` with Spring `ResponseEntity`\n\n### 8. **NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/qualifiers/NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper.java`\n- **Changes**: Replaced Jakarta CDI `@Qualifier` with Spring's `@Qualifier`\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated from Quarkus to Spring Boot conventions, maintaining the same functionality while using Spring Framework's dependency injection, security, and web layers."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"4fd1fd7d-1785-4fe0-b826-41261b13221b"}
