rg/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/ErrorResponse.java\n13. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/CommentResponse.java\n14. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/CommentsResponse.java\n\nAlso edit:\n15. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/user/UserModelBuilder.java\n    - Remove `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n    - Remove `@Named`\n\nDo all of these using the Edit tool. Read each file first, then edit it.\n\nIMPORTANT: The import line and the annotation line must both be removed. For the import, replace the import line with empty string. For the annotation, remove it from the annotation stack."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":869,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1074,"cache_read_input_tokens":145960,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1074,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1650},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"b1dc155b-3db5-4397-855f-d0c967f38390"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NTg7kicroDeM4p9mNLaddy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GRyFYjcpFhW6qzPzFyUbwP","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Update Dockerfile and start.sh","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. The project is at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output\n\nUpdate the start.sh and Dockerfile for Spring Boot.\n\n1. Read the file start.sh, then use the Write tool to overwrite it with:\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\n# Start PostgreSQL\npg_ctlcluster $(pg_lsclusters -h | head -1 | awk '{print $1, $2}') start\n\n# Create database and user\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE USER realworld WITH PASSWORD 'realworld';\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE DATABASE realworld OWNER realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE realworld TO realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\nexec java -jar target/realworldapiservice-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\n```\n\n2. The Dockerfile should stay largely the same since it uses Maven. Read the current Dockerfile, then update the build command if needed. The existing Dockerfile uses `mvn clean install -DskipTests` which should still work. Use Write to overwrite it with:\n```\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\n# install uv and PostgreSQL\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full postgresql postgresql-client \\\n    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\n# create venv and install\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest requests\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy all the assets\nCOPY . .\n\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\nRUN chmod +x start.sh\n\n# Build the application at image build time\nRUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n\nCMD [\"/app/start.sh\"]\n```\n\nNote: I added `requests` to the pip install command since the smoke test needs the requests library.\n\nUse the Write tool for both files."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":869,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1074,"cache_read_input_tokens":145960,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1074,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1650},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"9dc44d50-8c33-4b69-a57b-a26d57218024"}
