{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015zwLG7Ua4akyiWV4WENxVm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonFormat;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     5→import io.quarkus.runtime.annotations.RegisterForReflection;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import lombok.Getter;\n     9→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    10→import lombok.Setter;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→\n    13→@Getter\n    14→@Setter\n    15→@NoArgsConstructor\n    16→@JsonRootName(\"comment\")\n    17→@RegisterForReflection\n    18→public class CommentResponse {\n    19→\n    20→  private UUID id;\n    21→\n    22→  @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    23→  private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    24→\n    25→  @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    26→  private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    27→\n    28→  private String body;\n    29→  private ProfileResponse author;\n    30→\n    31→  public CommentResponse(Comment comment, ProfileResponse author) {\n    32→    this.id = comment.getId();\n    33→    this.createdAt = comment.getCreatedAt();\n    34→    this.updatedAt = comment.getUpdatedAt();\n    35→    this.body = comment.getBody();\n    36→    this.author = author;\n    37→  }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VMv4vrWvunu83Jk9vXwkEV","session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"f84c2d02-3307-42ee-b54f-94bb4da52935"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KxtnjbpYxNEXrdjhPa7CBk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.runtime.annotations.RegisterForReflection;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→\n     8→@Getter\n     9→@Setter\n    10→@RegisterForReflection\n    11→public class CommentsResponse {\n    12→\n    13→  private List<CommentResponse> comments;\n    14→\n    15→  public CommentsResponse(List<CommentResponse> comments) {\n    16→    this.comments = comments;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VMv4vrWvunu83Jk9vXwkEV","session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"3b5f25da-6d88-4cfd-8072-ce61c6a60f99"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Jxp3p3FKXDcn4QS2EGfu4a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→@Named\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class UserModelBuilder {\n    11→  private final ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    12→\n    13→  public User build(String username, String email, String password) {\n    14→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    15→        new User(UUID.randomUUID(), username, email, password, null, null));\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public User build(\n    19→      UUID id, String username, String bio, String image, String password, String email) {\n    20→    return modelValidator.validate(new User(id, username, email, password, bio, image));\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VMv4vrWvunu83Jk9vXwkEV","session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"9c18d599-3263-4ebb-b931-667b8cf452ed"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GRyFYjcpFhW6qzPzFyUbwP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully updated both files for your Spring Boot migration:\n\n## Updated Files\n\n### 1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/start.sh\n\n**Key change:** Line 12 was updated from:\n```bash\nexec java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar\n```\nto:\n```bash\nexec java -jar target/realworldapiservice-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\n```\n\nThis reflects the difference between Quarkus (which creates a `quarkus-app` directory structure) and Spring Boot (which creates a single executable JAR file).\n\n### 2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/Dockerfile\n\n**Key change:** Line 15 was updated to include the `requests` library:\n```dockerfile\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest requests\n```\n\nThis ensures the smoke test has access to the `requests` library it needs to make HTTP calls to test the API endpoints.\n\nBoth files retain their existing structure and functionality while being adapted for Spring Boot's different JAR packaging format and ensuring all necessary dependencies are available for testing."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"399b39f4-2845-4f22-98aa-fd2f8f5d53bf"}
