{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01M9yK189rs1zyTKraFYkp2x","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the problem. The primary ObjectMapper has WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled, and Spring MVC is using this ObjectMapper to serialize responses that don't have `@JsonRootName`. The `ArticlesResponse`, `CommentsResponse`, and `TagsResponse` classes don't use `@JsonRootName` - they're meant to be serialized without wrapping. \n\nThe issue is that the ArticlesResource uses `objectMapper.writeValueAsString()` for some endpoints but returns `ResponseEntity<String>` - but the TagsResource and some articles endpoints also serialize strings. However, the GET /articles endpoint returns a String which then gets double-wrapped by the primary ObjectMapper.\n\nWait, actually looking at the articles endpoint - it returns `ResponseEntity<String>` and uses `objectMapper.writeValueAsString()` with the `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper`. But the String itself gets wrapped by the primary ObjectMapper when Spring serializes it. The issue is that when Spring returns a String via `ResponseEntity<String>`, it still uses the primary ObjectMapper to serialize it, wrapping it again.\n\nLet me check - actually, `ResponseEntity<String>` should pass through without re-serialization since the content type is already set. The real issue is different - the `@Primary` ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE is being used by Spring MVC for the `ArticlesResponse` which doesn't have `@JsonRootName`, causing it to use the class name as root.\n\nLet me fix this properly:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":437,"cache_read_input_tokens":140886,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":437,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":449},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"d51841fa-de0c-4f2a-a287-f30d830d79c7"}
