{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Kk2dbKeDvr3wexzMX8NmR9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see! The Tags and Articles endpoints use `objectMapper.writeValueAsString()` with the noWrapRootValue ObjectMapper, then return the string. But Spring is re-serializing the string with the primary ObjectMapper that has WRAP_ROOT_VALUE. \n\nThe problem is that Spring MVC's HttpMessageConverter is being configured with the primary `@Primary ObjectMapper` that has `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`. This wraps ALL responses including those already serialized as strings.\n\nThe fix: I should NOT make the WRAP_ROOT_VALUE ObjectMapper the primary one. Instead, Spring MVC should use a normal ObjectMapper by default, and the individual endpoints that need wrapping should use the appropriate ObjectMapper. Let me also check the comments endpoint:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":776,"cache_read_input_tokens":141323,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":776,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":278},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"7754718d-92ca-4af7-b94a-cbbe05be993a"}
