{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UAbprvrXWFfhiDWRzxwxSe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is clear. The TagsResource and ArticlesResource serialize with `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper.writeValueAsString()` and return `ResponseEntity<String>`, but Spring MVC then re-serializes the String with the Primary ObjectMapper (which has WRAP_ROOT_VALUE). \n\nThe solution: I need to NOT set WRAP_ROOT_VALUE on the primary ObjectMapper. Instead, I should configure Spring to handle the wrapping differently. The proper way in Spring is to NOT use `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE/UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` globally, and handle the root wrapping at the individual response level.\n\nLet me fix the `ApplicationConfiguration` to not set `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` on the primary ObjectMapper, and instead configure the Jackson module to handle the root names properly with a custom approach:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":459,"cache_read_input_tokens":142099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":459,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":306},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"4a4c38e4-b761-47a5-b68c-1b1437232fed"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UAbprvrXWFfhiDWRzxwxSe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_0139okExgQLfGybCFRs9pKwh","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/configuration/ApplicationConfiguration.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":459,"cache_read_input_tokens":142099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":459,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":306},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"7ec27633-7ac2-42cb-8433-f093beae4fef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0139okExgQLfGybCFRs9pKwh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n     9→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n    10→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n    11→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Primary;\n    12→\n    13→@Configuration\n    14→public class ApplicationConfiguration {\n    15→\n    16→  @Bean\n    17→  public Slugify slugify() {\n    18→    return Slugify.builder().build();\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  @Bean\n    22→  @Primary\n    23→  public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n    24→    ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    25→    objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    26→    objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    27→    objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    28→    return objectMapper;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    32→  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n    33→  public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    34→    return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"023375ca-afe6-428d-91b1-2411636606cc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XHhuQn7uB4XmcvPB6S7j5V","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is: make the Primary ObjectMapper a normal one (no WRAP_ROOT_VALUE), keep the wrapping ObjectMapper as a named bean, and update the controllers to use the wrapping ObjectMapper where individual responses need wrapping (like article, user, etc.) and the noWrap one for lists. But actually, in Quarkus the original approach was that WRAP_ROOT_VALUE was enabled globally on JAX-RS, and the `@JsonRootName` annotations on response classes controlled the wrapping. In Spring MVC, using WRAP_ROOT_VALUE on the primary ObjectMapper wraps EVERYTHING including String responses.\n\nThe cleanest fix: Make the primary ObjectMapper NOT use WRAP_ROOT_VALUE. Instead, have the wrapping ObjectMapper as a separate bean. Then, for endpoints that need root wrapping (single entity responses), serialize with the wrapping ObjectMapper and return as String. For endpoints that already use noWrapRootValueObjectMapper, they already work.\n\nLet me look at which endpoints need wrapping vs not:\n\nThe original Quarkus app had WRAP_ROOT_VALUE globally. The responses with `@JsonRootName` like `UserResponse(\"user\")`, `ArticleResponse(\"article\")`, `ProfileResponse(\"profile\")`, `CommentResponse(\"comment\")`, `ErrorResponse(\"errors\")` get wrapped. The responses WITHOUT `@JsonRootName` like `ArticlesResponse`, `CommentsResponse`, `TagsResponse` were serialized by the noWrapRootValue mapper. \n\nThe fix: Make the primary Spring ObjectMapper NOT wrap, and update the controllers that return single entities to use the wrapping mapper. Let me update:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1151,"cache_read_input_tokens":142558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1151,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":923},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"42133553-2702-4828-87c9-2d52f4f7158c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XHhuQn7uB4XmcvPB6S7j5V","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_014ggnmoJeQPmSCfWQgzQEXo","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/configuration/ApplicationConfiguration.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\nimport com.github.slugify.Slugify;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Primary;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class ApplicationConfiguration {\n\n  @Bean\n  public Slugify slugify() {\n    return Slugify.builder().build();\n  }\n\n  @Bean(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n  public ObjectMapper wrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    return objectMapper;\n  }\n\n  @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n  public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n  }\n\n  @Bean\n  @Primary\n  public ObjectMapper primaryObjectMapper() {\n    ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    return objectMapper;\n  }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1151,"cache_read_input_tokens":142558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1151,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":923},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"009be269-cf40-4d91-87de-021da6599195"}
