{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The conversation is summarized below:\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the entire conversation:\n\n1. **Initial Request**: The user wants to migrate a Java application from Quarkus to Spring Boot. This is a comprehensive migration with specific requirements including Docker isolation, smoke tests, and CHANGELOG.md documentation.\n\n2. **Codebase Analysis Phase**: \n   - Explored the project structure - a RealWorld (Conduit) API with domain-driven design\n   - Key components: Users, Articles, Comments, Profiles, Tags\n   - Quarkus-specific: JAX-RS REST endpoints, Panache repositories, SmallRye JWT, CDI dependency injection, Elytron security\n   - Read all source files thoroughly\n\n3. **Migration Execution**:\n   - Created smoke.py test script\n   - Rewrote pom.xml (Quarkus BOM → Spring Boot parent)\n   - Created RealWorldApiApplication.java (Spring Boot main class)\n   - Rewrote application.properties (Quarkus → Spring Boot properties)\n   - Rewrote all 5 REST controllers (JAX-RS → Spring MVC)\n   - Rewrote ResourceUtils (SecurityContext → Principal)\n   - Rewrote all 8 repository classes (Panache → EntityManager)\n   - Rewrote EntityUtils (@ApplicationScoped → @Component)\n   - Rewrote all 5 configuration classes (CDI → Spring @Configuration/@Bean)\n   - Rewrote JwtTokenProvider (SmallRye → jjwt)\n   - Rewrote BCryptHashProvider (Elytron → Spring Security BCrypt)\n   - Rewrote SlugifySlugProvider (@ApplicationScoped → @Component)\n   - Created SecurityConfig (Spring Security filter chain)\n   - Created JwtAuthenticationFilter\n   - Rewrote ExceptionMappers (@ServerExceptionMapper → @RestControllerAdvice)\n   - Rewrote BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n   - Rewrote NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper qualifier\n   - Removed @RegisterForReflection from 14 model files\n   - Removed @Named from UserModelBuilder\n   - Updated Dockerfile and start.sh\n   - Removed old Quarkus test files\n\n4. **First Build & Test**:\n   - Docker build succeeded\n   - Container started successfully with Spring Boot\n   - Smoke tests: 8/11 passed, 3 failed\n   - Failures: Get Articles List, Get Comments, Get Tags - all \"Response missing X array\"\n\n5. **Diagnosis of Failures**:\n   - The primary ObjectMapper had WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled\n   - Spring MVC was using this primary ObjectMapper for ALL serialization\n   - List responses (ArticlesResponse, CommentsResponse, TagsResponse) without @JsonRootName were being wrapped with class name as root (e.g., \"ArticlesResponse\": {...})\n   - String responses from noWrapRootValueObjectMapper were being double-serialized\n\n6. **Fix Implementation** (most recent work):\n   - Updated ApplicationConfiguration.java to have 3 ObjectMapper beans:\n     - `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` - for wrapping single entities\n     - `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper` - for lists without wrapping\n     - `primaryObjectMapper` (@Primary) - plain, used by Spring MVC default\n   - Updated ALL controllers to:\n     - Use explicit ObjectMapper serialization\n     - Return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)`\n     - Use `wrapMapper` for single entities (user, article, comment, profile)\n     - Use `noWrapMapper` for lists (articles, comments, tags)\n     - Use constructor injection with `@Qualifier` instead of `@AllArgsConstructor`\n\n7. **Files modified in the fix round**:\n   - ApplicationConfiguration.java - added 3rd ObjectMapper bean\n   - UsersResource.java - complete rewrite with explicit serialization\n   - UserResource.java - complete rewrite with explicit serialization\n   - ArticlesResource.java - complete rewrite with explicit serialization\n   - ProfilesResource.java - complete rewrite with explicit serialization\n   - TagsResource.java was NOT updated in this round (still uses noWrapMapper, which should work)\n\n8. **Current State**: The controllers have been updated but the Docker image has NOT been rebuilt yet. Need to rebuild, restart, and rerun smoke tests.\n\n9. **Remaining Tasks**:\n   - Rebuild Docker image\n   - Run container\n   - Execute smoke tests\n   - Create CHANGELOG.md\n   - Write final migration report\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested a complete, autonomous migration of a Java RealWorld (Conduit) API application from Quarkus to Spring Boot. The migration must:\n   - Analyze the existing codebase and identify all framework-specific dependencies\n   - Generate smoke tests for original functionality\n   - Update all project configuration, dependencies, and build files\n   - Refactor all application code for Spring Boot APIs and patterns\n   - Modify Dockerfile for Spring Boot compilation/execution\n   - Build as Docker image, run container, execute smoke tests\n   - Use `$SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME` / `$SCARF_IMAGE_TAG` env vars and `-p 0:8080` for Docker isolation\n   - Document everything in `CHANGELOG.md`\n   - Complete in ONE SHOT without requesting additional input\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Quarkus → Spring Boot migration**: JAX-RS → Spring MVC, Panache → JPA EntityManager, CDI → Spring DI, SmallRye JWT → jjwt, Elytron BCrypt → Spring Security BCrypt\n   - **Domain-Driven Design**: Layered architecture with application (web), domain (features/models), infrastructure (repositories/providers/config)\n   - **RealWorld API spec**: Users, Articles, Comments, Profiles, Tags with JWT auth (\"Token\" prefix)\n   - **Jackson ObjectMapper WRAP_ROOT_VALUE**: Critical issue where `@JsonRootName` annotations control wrapping of single entities vs. list responses\n   - **Spring Security stateless JWT**: Custom `OncePerRequestFilter` extracting \"Token \" or \"Bearer \" prefixed JWTs\n   - **Docker isolation**: Dynamic port allocation with `-p 0:8080`, unique container/image names\n   - Environment variables: `SCARF_IMAGE_TAG=my_test_image_1`, `SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME=my_test_container_1`\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **pom.xml** - Migrated from Quarkus BOM to Spring Boot parent 3.4.1. Replaced all Quarkus deps (quarkus-rest-jackson, quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache, quarkus-smallrye-jwt, quarkus-elytron-security, etc.) with Spring Boot starters (web, data-jpa, validation, security, actuator) plus jjwt 0.12.6.\n\n   - **src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RealWorldApiApplication.java** - NEW: Spring Boot main class\n     ```java\n     @SpringBootApplication\n     public class RealWorldApiApplication {\n         public static void main(String[] args) {\n             SpringApplication.run(RealWorldApiApplication.class, args);\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/application.properties** - Migrated from Quarkus to Spring Boot properties:\n     ```properties\n     server.servlet.context-path=/api\n     server.port=8080\n     spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/realworld\n     spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     jwt.private-key-location=classpath:privateKey.pem\n     jwt.public-key-location=classpath:publicKey.pem\n     jwt.issuer=users-service\n     ```\n\n   - **ApplicationConfiguration.java** - Most recently updated to have 3 ObjectMapper beans to fix JSON serialization:\n     ```java\n     @Configuration\n     public class ApplicationConfiguration {\n       @Bean\n       public Slugify slugify() { return Slugify.builder().build(); }\n\n       @Bean(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n       public ObjectMapper wrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n         ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n         objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n         objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n         objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n         return objectMapper;\n       }\n\n       @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n       @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n       public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n         return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n       }\n\n       @Bean\n       @Primary\n       public ObjectMapper primaryObjectMapper() {\n         ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n         objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n         return objectMapper;\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **UsersResource.java** - Latest version uses explicit `wrapMapper` serialization:\n     ```java\n     @RestController\n     @RequestMapping(\"/users\")\n     public class UsersResource {\n       private final CreateUser createUser;\n       private final LoginUser loginUser;\n       private final JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n       private final ObjectMapper wrapMapper;\n\n       public UsersResource(CreateUser createUser, LoginUser loginUser,\n           JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider,\n           @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper wrapMapper) { ... }\n\n       @PostMapping(produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n       @Transactional\n       public ResponseEntity<String> create(...) throws JsonProcessingException {\n         final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.toCreateUserInput());\n         final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n         return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n             .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n             .body(wrapMapper.writeValueAsString(new UserResponse(user, token)));\n       }\n       // login similarly updated\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **UserResource.java** - Same pattern as UsersResource, uses `wrapMapper` for GET/PUT user\n\n   - **ArticlesResource.java** - Uses BOTH ObjectMappers via constructor injection:\n     ```java\n     public ArticlesResource(...,\n         @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapMapper,\n         @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper wrapMapper,\n         ResourceUtils resourceUtils) { ... }\n     ```\n     - `noWrapMapper` for: GET /articles, GET /feed, GET /{slug}/comments\n     - `wrapMapper` for: POST /articles, GET /{slug}, PUT /{slug}, POST /{slug}/comments, POST /{slug}/favorite, DELETE /{slug}/favorite\n\n   - **ProfilesResource.java** - Uses `wrapMapper` for all profile endpoints (GET, follow, unfollow)\n\n   - **TagsResource.java** - Uses `noWrapMapper` (was NOT updated in the latest round but already used correct approach)\n\n   - **ResourceUtils.java** - Changed to `@Component`, uses `java.security.Principal` instead of `SecurityContext`:\n     ```java\n     public UUID getLoggedUserId(Principal principal) {\n       return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **All 8 Repository classes** - Migrated from Panache to JPA EntityManager:\n     - `AbstractPanacheRepository` - now abstract class with `@PersistenceContext EntityManager`\n     - `UserRepositoryPanache`, `ArticleRepositoryPanache`, `TagRepositoryPanache`, `CommentRepositoryPanache`, `FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache`, `FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache`, `TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache` - all use `@Repository` and EntityManager queries\n\n   - **JwtTokenProvider.java** - Replaced SmallRye JWT with jjwt HMAC-SHA256:\n     ```java\n     @Component\n     public class JwtTokenProvider {\n       private static final String SECRET = \"realworld-api-secret-key-that-is-long-enough-for-hmac-sha256-algorithm-minimum-32-bytes\";\n       // createUserToken() and validateTokenAndGetSubject() using io.jsonwebtoken\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **BCryptHashProvider.java** - Uses `BCryptPasswordEncoder` from Spring Security\n\n   - **SecurityConfig.java** - NEW: Spring Security filter chain with JWT:\n     ```java\n     @Configuration @EnableWebSecurity\n     public class SecurityConfig {\n       @Bean\n       public SecurityFilterChain securityFilterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {\n         http.csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())\n             .sessionManagement(session -> session.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS))\n             .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth\n                 .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.POST, \"/users\", \"/users/login\").permitAll()\n                 .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.GET, \"/articles\", \"/articles/*\", \"/articles/*/comments\", \"/profiles/*\", \"/tags\").permitAll()\n                 .requestMatchers(\"/actuator/**\").permitAll()\n                 .anyRequest().authenticated())\n             .addFilterBefore(jwtAuthenticationFilter, UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter.class);\n         return http.build();\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **JwtAuthenticationFilter.java** - NEW: Extracts JWT from \"Token \" or \"Bearer \" header prefix\n\n   - **ExceptionMappers.java** - Changed from `@ServerExceptionMapper` to `@RestControllerAdvice` with `@ExceptionHandler`\n\n   - **BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java** - Changed from JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper<>` to `@RestControllerAdvice`\n\n   - **5 Configuration classes** (UsersConfiguration, ArticlesConfiguration, TagsConfiguration, CommentsConfiguration) - CDI `@Dependent/@Produces/@Singleton` → Spring `@Configuration/@Bean`\n\n   - **14 request/response model files** - Removed `@RegisterForReflection` and its import\n\n   - **UserModelBuilder.java** - Removed `@Named` and its import\n\n   - **Dockerfile** - Updated pip install to include `requests` library for smoke tests\n\n   - **start.sh** - Changed from `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar` to `java -jar target/realworldapiservice-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar`\n\n   - **smoke.py** - NEW: Python smoke test script testing 11 endpoints (register, login, get user, create article, get articles, get article by slug, create comment, get comments, get tags, get profile, favorite article)\n\n   - **src/test/** - Entire directory DELETED (contained Quarkus-specific integration tests)\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **Docker build env var error**: `docker build -t $SCARF_IMAGE_TAG .` failed because env var wasn't expanded. Fixed by using literal value `my_test_image_1`.\n   - **Bash syntax error**: Command substitution `$(...)` caused eval escaping issues. Fixed by running `docker port` separately and using the literal port value.\n   - **Smoke test failures (3/11)**: Get Articles List, Get Comments, Get Tags all returned \"Response missing X array\".\n     - Root cause: The `@Primary` ObjectMapper had `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled, causing Spring MVC to wrap ALL responses including `ResponseEntity<String>` content. List responses without `@JsonRootName` got wrapped with class name (e.g., `{\"ArticlesResponse\": {...}}` instead of `{\"articles\": [...]}`).\n     - Fix: Changed `ApplicationConfiguration` to have 3 ObjectMapper beans - plain `@Primary`, `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` for single entities, `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper` for lists. Updated ALL controllers to use explicit `objectMapper.writeValueAsString()` and return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)`.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully migrated all Quarkus-specific code to Spring Boot equivalents\n   - Resolved Panache → EntityManager repository migration with all complex queries (pagination, sorting, dynamic filters)\n   - Resolved JWT authentication from SmallRye (RSA keys) to jjwt (HMAC-SHA256)\n   - Resolved Jackson serialization wrapping issue by separating ObjectMapper responsibilities\n   - Docker image builds and Spring Boot starts successfully on port 8080 with context path `/api`\n   - 8/11 smoke tests passed on first run; the 3 failures were diagnosed and fix code was written but NOT yet rebuilt/tested\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - Message 1: Comprehensive migration instructions from Quarkus to Spring Boot with detailed checklist, Docker isolation requirements, migration workflow steps, validation protocol, error handling guidelines, and output format requirements.\n   - Message 2: (Empty/system reminder about TodoWrite - no explicit user content)\n   - Message 3: (Empty/system reminder about TodoWrite - no explicit user content)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Rebuild Docker image with the ObjectMapper/controller fixes\n   - Run container and re-execute smoke tests to verify all 11 pass\n   - Fix any remaining test failures\n   - Create `CHANGELOG.md` documenting all actions, errors, and resolutions\n   - Write final migration report in the specified format (Migration Summary, File Tree, Step-by-Step Log, CHANGELOG.md Contents, Error Handling)\n\n8. Current Work:\n   Immediately before this summary, I had just finished writing the updated controller files to fix the Jackson ObjectMapper WRAP_ROOT_VALUE serialization issue. Specifically:\n   - Updated `ApplicationConfiguration.java` with 3 ObjectMapper beans\n   - Rewrote `UsersResource.java` with explicit `wrapMapper` serialization\n   - Rewrote `UserResource.java` with explicit `wrapMapper` serialization\n   - Rewrote `ArticlesResource.java` with both `wrapMapper` and `noWrapMapper`\n   - Rewrote `ProfilesResource.java` with explicit `wrapMapper` serialization\n   - `TagsResource.java` was NOT updated (already correctly uses `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper`)\n   \n   These changes have been written to disk but the Docker image has NOT been rebuilt yet. The container running is still the OLD version.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Rebuild the Docker image and re-run the smoke tests to verify the ObjectMapper fix resolves all 3 failing tests. Per the migration checklist: \"Build the application as a Docker image, run the container to ensure the service starts successfully, and execute any generated smoke tests against or within running container to verify the migrated application behaves as expected. Address any errors that arise and repeat steps as needed.\"\n   \n   Concrete commands needed:\n   ```bash\n   docker rm -f my_test_container_1\n   docker build -t my_test_image_1 .\n   docker run -d --name my_test_container_1 -p 0:8080 my_test_image_1\n   # Get port and run smoke tests\n   ```\n   Then create CHANGELOG.md and write the final migration report..\nPlease continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"021059be-2278-4ae3-9beb-759f663e5ea1","isSynthetic":true}
