{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Csu7iaYZqwzWkFGHPbqZgB","type":"tool_result","content":"2026-03-14T11:24:55.321Z  WARN 1 --- [nio-8080-exec-2] .w.s.m.s.DefaultHandlerExceptionResolver : Resolved [org.springframework.http.converter.HttpMessageNotReadableException: JSON parse error: Unrecognized field \"user\" (class org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequest), not marked as ignorable]\n2026-03-14T11:24:55.355Z  WARN 1 --- [nio-8080-exec-4] .w.s.m.s.DefaultHandlerExceptionResolver : Resolved [org.springframework.http.converter.HttpMessageNotReadableException: JSON parse error: Unrecognized field \"user\" (class org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.LoginRequest), not marked as ignorable]\n2026-03-14T11:25:01.606Z  WARN 1 --- [nio-8080-exec-4] .w.s.m.s.DefaultHandlerExceptionResolver : Resolved [org.springframework.http.converter.HttpMessageNotReadableException: JSON parse error: Unrecognized field \"user\" (class org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequest), not marked as ignorable]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"d5e32b99-0762-46f3-9eca-5e084c6946d3"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0185yPsZmLAJ7Xvjhkzuw3eH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is clear now. The request body has `{\"user\": {...}}` wrapping, but the `NewUserRequest` class expects the unwrapped version. This is because:\n1. The `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` was previously the `@Primary` mapper and was being used by Spring MVC for request deserialization (which had `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled)\n2. Now that `@Primary` is a plain ObjectMapper, it doesn't unwrap the root value\n\nThe RealWorld API spec sends `{\"user\": {...}}` for user endpoints, `{\"article\": {...}}` for article endpoints, and `{\"comment\": {...}}` for comment endpoints. These have `@JsonRootName` annotations on them, but the primary ObjectMapper doesn't unwrap.\n\nLet me check the request models:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":477,"cache_read_input_tokens":64418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":477,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":302},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"2185f269-71ea-4329-8976-b2273a18c1d5"}
