{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X8TLFhkS4UeJg8aryLt4mZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import java.util.UUID;\n     6→import lombok.Getter;\n     7→import lombok.Setter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.NewCommentInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→@JsonRootName(\"comment\")\n    14→public class NewCommentRequest {\n    15→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    16→  private String body;\n    17→\n    18→  public NewCommentInput toNewCommentInput(UUID authorId, String articleSlug) {\n    19→    return new NewCommentInput(authorId, articleSlug, this.body);\n    20→  }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"02a73323-141a-4132-8411-e7e69ae5eb89"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FPvjmJJwwarPf7SaGgsg9w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Email;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import lombok.Getter;\n     8→import lombok.Setter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n    12→\n    13→@Getter\n    14→@Setter\n    15→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    16→@AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull\n    17→public class UpdateUserRequest {\n    18→\n    19→  @Pattern(regexp = \"\\\\A(?!\\\\s*\\\\Z).+\", message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    20→  private String username;\n    21→\n    22→  private String bio;\n    23→  private String image;\n    24→  @Email private String email;\n    25→\n    26→  public UpdateUserInput toUpdateUserInput(UUID userId) {\n    27→    return new UpdateUserInput(userId, this.username, this.bio, this.image, this.email);\n    28→  }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"502aa395-3018-48dc-bb87-5a63361a2629"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JaxfxfPtWEVvh1VmqidzYy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Setter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.UpdateArticleInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→@NoArgsConstructor\n    14→@JsonRootName(\"article\")\n    15→@AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull\n    16→public class UpdateArticleRequest {\n    17→\n    18→  private String title;\n    19→\n    20→  private String description;\n    21→\n    22→  private String body;\n    23→\n    24→  public UpdateArticleInput toUpdateArticleInput(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    25→    return new UpdateArticleInput(authorId, slug, this.title, this.description, this.body);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"b1495cc8-3d50-45c8-bfe7-66e6684fca10"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_018Ks18ygED8pmbyyf3QVuEr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. All request models use `@JsonRootName` for wrapping/unwrapping (e.g., `@JsonRootName(\"user\")` on `NewUserRequest`). The original Quarkus setup used `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` on the ObjectMapper for deserialization, so `{\"user\": {...}}` was unwrapped automatically.\n\nThe fix is to make the `@Primary` ObjectMapper also unwrap root values for deserialization. But that would break things because Spring MVC uses the primary ObjectMapper for both serialization AND deserialization. If we enable `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` on the primary, it would wrap all responses.\n\nThe better approach is to configure Spring's `MappingJackson2HttpMessageConverter` to use the `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` for both reading and writing request/response bodies, since our controllers already manually serialize to String. Actually wait - our controllers return `ResponseEntity<String>`, so Spring MVC uses `StringHttpMessageConverter`, not Jackson's converter. This means the primary ObjectMapper is only used for *deserializing* request bodies.\n\nSo the fix is to make the primary ObjectMapper enable `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` for deserialization only (not `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`):"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3535,"cache_read_input_tokens":65982,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3535,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":860},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"4e339b48-6e70-4ec6-90c5-31c72a7eed15"}
