{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WYtiKvEPNLVm39ktncRgzM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I also need to check: does the GET `/profiles/{username}` endpoint need authentication? Let me check the SecurityConfig again. The GET `/profiles/*` is permitted, so that should work. But the smoke test showed \"No response\" for Get Profile. Let me also check the actual error for the profile request after fixing deserialization. Also, there might be an issue with the `/articles/*/comments` pattern not matching nested paths. Let me also update SecurityConfig to also permit GET on `/articles/{slug}/comments` using a more precise pattern:\n\nActually wait - the profile endpoint returned \"No response\" which means the requests library itself failed. Let me first focus on the deserialization fix since that's the root cause for most failures. Let me rebuild and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":71514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":368,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":293},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e551caab-c624-46bd-b50e-a080c0cd7305","uuid":"8104762a-0d45-44b5-a06b-5d1b16e0d216"}
